==English==

===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From Old French [[pantere]] (modern [[panthère]]), from Latin [[panthera]], from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[πάνθηρ]]''' {{italbrac|panther}}, probably of Oriental origin.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# Any of various [[big cat]]s with black fur.
# Any big cat of the genus ''[[Panthera]]''.

